Description: SchoolEdge Mobile was founded to fix one specific problem. The conversation that parents have with their kids each night.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Detroit Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: The conversation that parents have with their kids each night about homework and school is broken.  In that conversation, the student holds the power because they have the information.  To this point there has never been an effective and realistic way to communicate to parents what a student's homework is every day.  Parents simply don't know.  ParentEdge® fixes that.  Every night at a specific time it sends a homework text message and an email directly to parents telling them what their child's work is for the night. Parents don't have to log into a website, they don't have to check a blog, or even check their email if they want.  All they have to do is check their cell phone when they get a text.

Full Description: CAD Audio originally took shape as the Astatic Corporation in 1931, founded by C.M. Chorpening and F.H. Woodworth, two ham radio operators who needed a static-free microphone for their transmitters. They worked with local engineers to develop the company’s first crystal radio microphone, the model D-104. Having overcome the problem of static—hence the company name “Astatic”— and improved the quality of radio transmitter microphones in general, Chorpening and Woodworth went on to incorporate in 1933 and develop a line of innovative crystal mics, phonograph pickups and recording heads. Astatic also made significant contributions to the allied effort in World War II with an underwater sound detection hydrophone and static-discharger for Army and Navy aircraft.

Control Development, Inc. introduced the world’s first commercial, PC plug-in miniature spectrometer in 1991. This spectrometer was a silicon CCD-based device, covering the UV to near NIR spectral range. Control Development also introduced the world’s first PC plug-in miniature, NIR spectrometer using a thermo-electrically cooled InGaAs array. Control Development’s principals bring a combined 82 years of experience in high tech, electronics, electro-optics, optics, and software design, including military and pharmaceutical applications. Description: Mirra (formerly Ispiri) is a software, services & appliance company focused on providing solutions for personal digital content management.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Mirra, Inc. (formerly Ispiri, Inc.) is a software, services and appliance company focused on providing solutions for personal digital content management. In September 2003, Mirra announced the Mirra Personal Server, designed for consumer and small office/home office (SOHO) professionals who need a simple and affordable way to protect, remotely access and share their files, photos, email and other important digital content. The Mirra Personal Server made its debut at the prestigious DEMOmobile Conference, where it won a DEMOgods award. Mirra began shipping to customers online and through select Best Buy Co. stores in December 2003. The Company plans to implement its national retail rollout in Q1 and Q2 of 2004.  As consumers and SOHO professionals acquire digital cameras, adopt broadband and implement wireless networking at a rapid pace, they're discovering that their digital files, email and photos are increasing in value and volume, requiring simpler, more reliable ways to protect their data. And their growing reliance on digital content calls for new ways to share and access it. In the end, our personal digital content is more valuable, and irreplaceable, than our PCs - and we want it protected and accessible from anywhere, at any time. To date, there have been no easy solutions that address the increasingly complex issues faced by consumers and SOHO professionals - or solutions that haven't also required the help of a "smart cousin" or professional IT advisor. Mirra Personal Server serves that need, we believe. Mirra, Inc. is a privately held company in Mountain View, California.
Industry Groups: Commerce and Shopping, Information Technology, Software

Description: A Baton Rouge, La.-based supplier of synthetic rubber to the industrial and tire markets
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: East West Copolymer's (formerly Lion Copolymer) SBR/NBR site has been a landmark of Baton Rouge, Louisiana, since the 1940s.  The facility was designed and built by the U.S. Government during World War II, and since then has played a major role in the development and advancement in synthetic rubber technology. Operations of the SBR facility began in 1943 with a hot emulsion polymerization process.  Soon after, in 1948, the facility retooled its operations and developed the first cold polymerization plant in North America.  This allowed for better process control and end physical properties of most grades of SBR rubber.  With almost two decades passing, the Baton Rouge facility then designed and modified part of its facility to produce NBR grades of rubber, completing this effort in 1965.
Top 5 Investors: Main Street Capital, Trive Capital Holdings, TerraMar Capital

Description: Helicon Therapeutics discovers therapeutics to treat disorders of cognition through genetic basis of long-term memory formation.
Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Helicon Therapeutics is a privately held Company formed to discover therapeutics to treat disorders of cognition through an understanding of the genetic basis of long-term memory formation. The scientific origin and founding intellectual property came from the neuroscience program at the Cold Spring Harbor Laboratory.  Through seminal studies of learning and memory in fruit flies, a key function of the CREB (cAMP Response Element Binding Protein) gene was defined for the first time. The CREB gene encodes a protein which regulates the biochemical pathway that converts short-term memory to long-term memory - and it appears to function similarly in both fruit fly and in man.  Further functional genomic studies have identified a large number of additional genes that participate in this (and parallel) memory pathway(s). All of these genes are potential targets for the production of drugs that enhance or diminish memory formation.
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering

Description: A certified Managing General Agency serving independent agents throughout the southeast for over fifty years.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Southern Insurance Underwriters, Inc. (SIU), based in Alpharetta, Georgia, is a certified Managing General Agency serving independent agents throughout the southeast for over fifty years. On July 1, 1964, W.C. Duesenberg, Sr. purchased the Atlanta branch office of Kurt Hitke & Company and created Southern Insurance Underwriters, Inc. Building on the foundation started by Mr. Hitke, SIU specialized in Non-Standard Auto coverage and other specialty coverages including Commercial Trucking and Senior Drivers. Over fifty years later, the list of coverages has expanded to include: Commercial Property & Casualty, Commercial Transportation, Personal Property, Professional Lines and Standard Lines. SIU offers a broad range of property, casualty, and transportation products and specializes in hard to place, specialty and excess & surplus lines risks. With an experienced staff of underwriters, the scope of risks that can be underwritten ranges from the simplest property risks to highly sophisticated self-insured programs. Today, SIU represents more than 150 admitted and non-admitted specialty companies, Lloyd’s of London, and several standard companies.
